In article <cistron.200001131010.PAA15375@gem.wipinfo.soft.net>,
T V Govind  <thiruvengada.govindan@wipro.com> wrote:
>	Does anybody know of how to setup a remote console on linux. The
>	documentation talks about setting up a serial console.
Read /usr/src/linux/Documentation/serial-console.txt, and make sure
that your kernel was compiled with serial console support turned on.
>       i am trying to
>	get linux on a box thats only got a serial port. i have setup the
>	machine with a null-modem cable and have connected it to the serial
>	port of another machine running linux (both running  2.2.15).
Euh.. kernel 2.2.15 doesn't exist yet, latest is 2.2.14 which was released
a week ago or so.
Mike.
